rComments: I feel blessed to find this prof for a D level psych course. No presentation save me from anxiety and depression. This prof is a gem of a person.
Honestly one of THE best professors I have ever had. Extremely knowledgable, understanding, and helpful! Was my second course taken with him :)

Extremely knowledgeable and well-rounded prof. The material was really boring considering, but he really did his best to make it entertaining. I loved my TA too, he was super helpful. The assignments and tests are fair, and honestly really helpful for future higher level courses. Would take a class with him again, not only because he's hot lol.

He seems fairly professional and casual. He understands materials he is teaching and you will get good answers if you ask questions. Instructions for term assignments are very clear and you can ask TAs for extra help. There is a lot of reading and it may seem tedious but I found the course very useful for all psych students.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Considering that the course was dry, I'm impressed that the lectures didn't bore me to death. He's an excellent speaker and is very passionate about his work. The exams and assignments were straightforward and he offers a lot of assistance along the way. He's also very approachable. It's evident that he takes interest in the efforts of his students
One of the best profs at UTSC. He knows what he's talking about and most definitely a fair marker. Its hard to focus in that class though, because he's so great looking. You can easily get distracted

Loved the course and the prof. Excellent teaching methods, textbook put to good use. Yes a lot of reading but worth it. He engages the class in interesting ways, always looking forward to going to class. Has mini discussions. He's passionate and very knowledgeable. Your overall grade will definitely be reflected on how hard you work in the class

This class was quite tough! There was SO much reading, it was ridiculous! He's a decent lecturer, but the course tested you on the most random things ever. Each chapter had to have been apx 120 pages with tones of small information. But pay attention to lectures, because he tests you a lot about lecture information so it is a bonus.
i took two classes with him and both classes i enjoyed. He is a great prof i recommend his class... :)
